00:24:38.053 --> 00:24:38.381
I don't want any of my kids to go to hell, either.

00:24:38.381 --> 00:24:46.480
" His heart is after leaving the ninety-nine to go after the one.

00:24:46.480 --> 00:24:53.040
He said, "I don't want any of my kids to go to hell, Brandon.

00:24:53.040 --> 00:24:53.760
Neither would you.

00:24:53.760 --> 00:24:54.880
None of them.

00:24:54.880 --> 00:25:04.159
" If you knew that Braden was going to hell, or PA, whoever, and you were watching it as a father and you're going, "Oh, no, my babies!

00:25:04.699 --> 00:25:06.818
" And that's why he said, "I want this harvest.

00:25:06.818 --> 00:25:19.800
" And he said, "If you just do your job and walk and take your authority and do what I've commissioned you to do on YouTube and pray, if you all will do this, I'll come back and get you.

00:25:19.800 --> 00:25:23.093
But I'm coming back for a harvest.

00:25:26.823 --> 00:25:29.920
" And I saw a gauge, like I said, and I said, "Lord, well, how many do you want?

00:25:29.920 --> 00:25:31.520
" because that's my mind.

00:25:31.520 --> 00:25:32.853
There's a bunch of them.

00:25:32.853 --> 00:25:35.510
The tribulation is going to have people in it, right?

00:25:35.510 --> 00:25:39.509
So I said, "Well, I'm thinking, 'Well, how many do we have to get?

00:25:39.509 --> 00:25:40.880
What's the harvest number?

00:25:40.880 --> 00:25:41.749
'" Five billion.

00:25:41.749 --> 00:25:44.249
Five billion was the number I heard in my spirit—over five billion.

00:25:46.907 --> 00:25:47.476
I know there's eight billion, but five was like, "Believe big.

00:25:47.476 --> 00:25:49.320
" Five billion folks, five billion people.

00:25:58.840 --> 00:25:59.040
A radical move of God for a harvest of over five billion.

00:25:59.040 --> 00:26:01.662
To me, I'm like, "Whoa, okay, let's do it.

00:26:01.662 --> 00:26:03.867
" Nothing's too big for God.

00:26:03.867 --> 00:26:17.719
If we just believe, if we start plugging away and start doing what we're supposed to do, use our authority, and pray into this thing as raising up a million-person prayer army of men and women, praying and asking the Lord to send the laborers.

00:26:17.719 --> 00:26:23.775
He said, "For the harvest is plentiful, and the laborers are few.

00:26:23.775 --> 00:26:25.760
" Do you understand?

00:26:25.760 --> 00:26:31.787
There's a lot of people that just go, "Well, you know, it seems like too much.

00:26:31.787 --> 00:26:33.726
I like doing my status quo.

00:26:33.726 --> 00:26:44.400
I like watching my soap opera," or whatever they like to do, "and eat my bonbons and ice cream because I just like my own family time.

00:26:44.400 --> 00:26:45.573
It's not convenient.

00:26:45.573 --> 00:26:46.159
" That's what I told you.

00:26:46.159 --> 00:26:48.080
It's not going to be convenient church.

00:26:48.080 --> 00:26:52.980
And what he also showed me was—what is the word that we looked up today?

00:26:52.980 --> 00:26:53.580
Nepotism.

00:26:53.580 --> 00:26:54.180
Nepotism.

00:26:54.180 --> 00:26:56.933
He says, "It's not about nepotism.

00:26:56.933 --> 00:27:02.640
" You see a lot of ministry with nepotism as the elders, because he's talking about the elders going home.

00:27:05.627 --> 00:27:06.640
And he said, "Well, it doesn't just fall on the next generation, Brandon.

00:27:08.879 --> 00:27:11.680
They may go into it knowing, 'I have this name,' but you don't sustain yourself there.

00:27:11.680 --> 00:27:12.629
It's by refining fire.

00:27:14.080 --> 00:27:14.259
" And he was warning me.

00:27:24.071 --> 00:27:24.293
He said, "Nepotism is poisonous in ministry.

00:27:24.293 --> 00:27:32.799
" So what I'm trying to tell you is, you don't think you're qualified, and you don't think God can use you, but it's all hands on deck.

00:27:32.799 --> 00:27:50.491
And just because you may think, "Well, my pastor has a son or a daughter, and it's surely going to go on them, and he's going to use them," but I'm telling you folks, you may think, "Well, I'm not qualified.

00:27:50.491 --> 00:27:52.148
God can't use me.

00:27:57.360 --> 00:28:01.280
" But if you just have a yielded 'yes' and your heart is right before him, he said it's all hands on deck.

00:28:01.280 --> 00:28:08.373
And it's not going to be just because of nepotism, like, "Well, they've been in ministry their whole life, and it's been generational.

00:28:16.649 --> 00:28:16.899
" That's baloney.

00:28:16.899 --> 00:28:20.088
If you just have a heart and you say, "God, here am I.

00:28:20.088 --> 00:28:22.027
Use me," he'll use you.

00:28:22.027 --> 00:28:24.080
That's what I'm trying to say.

00:28:24.080 --> 00:28:28.766
And a lot of times people say, "Well, Brandon, who are you?

00:28:28.766 --> 00:28:30.137
You're not qualified.

00:28:30.137 --> 00:28:32.299
Where did you go to Bible school?

00:28:32.299 --> 00:28:34.240
Where did you go to this?

00:28:34.464 --> 00:28:35.248
" I went to the school of hard knocks.

00:28:35.248 --> 00:28:38.629
Let me tell you where I went to school: I went to the school of hard knocks.

00:28:38.903 --> 00:28:56.270
And I may not be this Bible scholar out there—I know I read the word, I have it playing in my background, and I've had learning disabilities my whole life—but I was just a man who was a janitor that said, "God, here am I.

00:28:56.270 --> 00:28:57.020
Use me.

00:29:07.699 --> 00:29:09.965
" And he said, "Brandon, go on YouTube, tell people I'm coming.

00:29:18.222 --> 00:29:18.498
" And I said, "Father, I'll do it.

00:29:18.498 --> 00:29:19.954
" And here I am.

00:29:19.954 --> 00:29:28.350
I'm sitting on a couch in the middle of my bedroom, and I have some lights I got off of Amazon, and I've got my iPhone right here recording me.

00:29:34.529 --> 00:29:35.279
It doesn't take a studio with multi-million dollar cameras and multi-million dollar lights for you to be used by God.

00:29:42.301 --> 00:29:52.320
I just got a little iPhone, and I have a green screen behind me with the revival playing so that it looks pretty for you.

00:29:52.320 --> 00:29:59.416
But I'm here to tell you, if you just say yes to Jesus today, it doesn't matter how much money you think you have.

00:29:59.416 --> 00:30:09.019
I've got less than a thousand-dollar iPhone that I'm making payments on every single month, but I say, "Jesus, here am I.

00:30:10.950 --> 00:30:18.559
" So I'm trying to tell you, don't think yourself too small that God can't use you, because I was the guy that was just in the bathroom cleaning toilets not even a couple of years ago.

00:30:18.559 --> 00:30:23.849
And I thought nobody would even look my direction.

00:30:23.849 --> 00:30:37.919
And now, all of a sudden, I've got people calling me from all around the world saying, "Hey, we want to talk to you.

00:30:37.919 --> 00:30:41.760
" And I'm like, "Where were you a couple of years ago?

00:30:43.093 --> 00:30:43.467
" I'm still the same guy.

00:30:43.840 --> 00:30:51.783
I just want to pray and tell everybody that Jesus loves them and he has a plan for their life.

00:31:13.130 --> 00:31:13.420
Just like I told Diana, I said, "If I had to go back to cleaning bathrooms tomorrow, I'd do it because that's where I died.

00:31:13.420 --> 00:31:18.850
" That's where Brandon found out how to hear the voice of the Lord—at the commode.

00:31:18.850 --> 00:31:22.146
Listening to him through the hardest times of my life.

00:31:22.146 --> 00:31:26.790
I never had someone give me a tip of the hat, saying, "Boy, you got what it takes.

00:31:26.790 --> 00:31:28.159
" Most people always said, "You didn't.

00:31:28.159 --> 00:31:30.560
" They didn't believe in me.

00:31:30.560 --> 00:31:31.644
Nobody did.

00:31:48.592 --> 00:31:48.776
But I'm telling you, Jesus did.

00:31:59.378 --> 00:31:59.627
And Jesus believes in you.

00:32:08.384 --> 00:32:08.688
And if He'll use me, He'll use you.

00:32:08.688 --> 00:32:16.747
So, if you've got to get a camera out there and put your iPhone up with a little stand on it from Amazon and say, "Hey, here am I.

00:32:16.747 --> 00:32:18.023
I'm out there.

00:32:18.023 --> 00:32:19.600
I've got something to say.

00:32:19.600 --> 00:32:21.760
I want to tell you about Jesus.

00:32:21.760 --> 00:32:24.986
I'll tell you about my life today," that's what we did.

00:32:24.986 --> 00:32:37.509
I had a vision, and the more I pray—it's like I told my friend Gina, I said, "I pray, and now I'm driving around and God takes me to the future.

00:32:37.509 --> 00:32:43.770
I see sometimes five years in advance, and He'll show me things that are coming.

00:32:43.770 --> 00:32:47.893
" He said, "This is what I want you to pray.

00:32:50.103 --> 00:32:50.445
" And I'll be in that scene.

00:32:50.445 --> 00:32:54.377
I know what's going to happen at that point, a couple of years away.

00:33:00.600 --> 00:33:00.860
And it's developing more and more as I yield to Him and just say, "Yes, Lord.

00:33:00.860 --> 00:33:01.899
Here am I.

00:33:01.899 --> 00:33:02.337
Use me.

00:33:18.619 --> 00:33:18.799
" I'm telling you, it wasn't somebody special with some big degree or somebody huge in ministry saying, "Brandon, I believe in you, boy.

00:33:27.379 --> 00:33:28.728
You've got what it takes.

00:33:28.728 --> 00:33:30.984
" Not one time.

00:33:30.984 --> 00:33:31.248
Not one time.

00:33:37.472 --> 00:33:37.728
I had people prophesy over us, but they all look at you like you're crazy.

00:33:37.984 --> 00:33:43.919
I see visions and the Lord shows me things, but when they start coming to pass, they go, "There's maybe something to this boy.

00:33:46.409 --> 00:33:46.764
" I said, "Well, I just love Jesus.

00:33:46.764 --> 00:33:47.880
I just love Jesus.

00:33:57.858 --> 00:33:58.080
" And as far as having a huge platform of everybody wanting to say that, the fakers come out wanting to be your friend now.

00:34:02.810 --> 00:34:03.020
And then you go, "Come on, man.

00:34:09.500 --> 00:34:09.960
I can see through that.

00:34:26.839 --> 00:34:27.279
I can see through that.

00:34:27.279 --> 00:34:32.948
" But I want to tell you, Jesus saw it the whole time.

00:34:33.130 --> 00:34:39.182
And you don't need anybody to tip their hat to you and say, "You can do it.

00:34:39.182 --> 00:34:41.942
" All you need to do is say, "Jesus, here am I.

00:34:41.942 --> 00:34:42.457
Use me.

00:34:42.457 --> 00:34:48.020
" It's all hands on deck right now, is what I'm trying to tell you.

00:34:48.020 --> 00:34:51.239
You may be in the back of a nursery room helping out with the children's church.

00:35:06.266 --> 00:35:06.479
You may be the guy that's picking the weeds in the flower bed at the church.

00:35:21.120 --> 00:35:21.440
I was both: going in there, cleaning the diapers up, doing it all, vomit spills.

00:35:21.440 --> 00:35:25.371
Did it for years—15 years of my life.

00:35:25.371 --> 00:35:37.269
Cleaned up poo all over the floor, elderly losing their bowels, walking in there and cleaning up, and you have so much it would gag a maggot.

00:35:47.920 --> 00:35:48.263
That's how bad it was.

00:35:59.680 --> 00:36:00.000
You would throw up all over the place, and I'd be gagging trying to clean up people's waste.

00:36:00.000 --> 00:36:02.340
But I'd just say, "God, here am I.

00:36:02.340 --> 00:36:03.060
Mold me.

00:36:07.760 --> 00:36:08.046
You can use me.

00:36:08.046 --> 00:36:11.090
If You can use this man, I'll do something for You.

00:36:11.090 --> 00:36:18.240
" So I just have this on my heart to tell you when I hear the Lord tell me, "Brandon, I'll come back.

00:36:18.240 --> 00:36:19.440
I want the souls.

00:36:19.440 --> 00:36:20.160
I'm waiting.

00:36:20.160 --> 00:36:21.119
I want Asia.

00:36:21.119 --> 00:36:22.959
I'm calling out for Asia.

00:36:27.860 --> 00:36:28.040
" But nothing happens in the natural until it's birthed out of the supernatural in prayer.

00:36:28.040 --> 00:36:28.400
Nothing.

00:36:28.400 --> 00:36:31.760
Everything is always birthed out of prayer.

00:36:35.017 --> 00:36:35.211
And so we must pray.

00:36:35.211 --> 00:36:42.889
I've talked too much today again, but I don't know, maybe that blessed you, maybe it didn't, but I just thought I should tell you.

00:36:47.849 --> 00:36:48.107
I just have a heart after people and I see them so broken every single day.

00:36:48.107 --> 00:36:58.589
When you're driving around, you see the homeless and they're tweaking out on drugs, and you just look at it and you go, "Man, there's a better way.

00:36:58.589 --> 00:37:01.680
God has so much more for you.

00:37:01.680 --> 00:37:07.040
He loves you and He has a plan for your life.

00:37:07.040 --> 00:37:07.680
" Do you understand?

00:37:07.680 --> 00:37:18.409
There are so many people who have been so religiously brainwashed that we don't realize how much Jesus Christ truly loves us and He has a plan for our lives.

00:37:18.409 --> 00:37:27.540
But religion, the Pharisees always try to tell you you're not good enough: "Well, you have sin in your life.

00:37:27.540 --> 00:37:29.580
He can't use you.

00:37:31.960 --> 00:37:35.440
" You know, we live upright and we try to live holy as He is holy.

00:37:35.440 --> 00:37:41.040
But when we fall down and skin our knee, we pick ourselves back up.

00:37:41.040 --> 00:37:42.640
God is always there and ever-present.

00:37:42.640 --> 00:37:46.464
He's an ever-present help in a time of need.

00:37:48.286 --> 00:37:56.560
And He has His hands ready to wrap around us like the prodigal son saying, "Hey, you got this.

00:37:56.560 --> 00:37:58.309
You can do this.

00:37:58.309 --> 00:38:04.674
" But most people always try to disqualify you the moment they see you: "Well, he talks too much.

00:38:16.853 --> 00:38:17.280
Well, he looks a certain way.

00:38:17.280 --> 00:38:18.240
He's too overweight.

00:38:18.240 --> 00:38:18.480
He's this.

00:38:18.480 --> 00:38:19.200
He's that.

00:38:19.200 --> 00:38:21.736
" You say, "No, God looks at the heart.

00:38:21.736 --> 00:38:24.304
" David was the one picked last.

00:38:24.304 --> 00:38:32.600
All the other sons were picked first, and they were looking at them going, "Man, they've got what it takes.

00:38:36.320 --> 00:38:36.740
" And the prophet said, "Nope, not him.

00:38:36.740 --> 00:38:38.000
Not him.

00:38:38.000 --> 00:38:39.260
Not him.

00:38:39.260 --> 00:38:40.480
Not him.

00:38:40.480 --> 00:38:42.937
Do you have anybody else?

00:38:42.937 --> 00:38:53.040
" "Well, we do, but he's on the backside over there and he's tending the sheep.

00:39:07.200 --> 00:39:07.383
We're not too proud of him.

00:39:07.383 --> 00:39:11.440
He's the one that everybody kind of looks down on.

00:39:11.440 --> 00:39:12.891
He's kind of weird.

00:39:12.891 --> 00:39:14.320
He plays his harp.

00:39:14.320 --> 00:39:15.938
He's kind of different, you know.

00:39:23.459 --> 00:39:23.799
" And he goes, "Bring him to me.

00:39:23.799 --> 00:39:28.720
" He goes over there, looks at him, and goes, "You're the one.

00:39:28.720 --> 00:39:35.840
You're the one playing the harp, taking care of the sheep that smell like sheep poop.

00:39:35.840 --> 00:39:38.671
" That's the one that God uses.

00:39:38.671 --> 00:39:41.383
So I'm just trying to encourage you.

00:39:41.383 --> 00:39:44.013
Don't get down on yourself.

00:39:44.013 --> 00:39:48.533
I'm trying to say all that to say: just keep on keeping on.

00:39:48.533 --> 00:39:50.293
You've got what it takes.

00:40:05.540 --> 00:40:05.830
And God chose you for such a time as this.

00:40:18.600 --> 00:40:18.864
In these last days, it's all hands on deck.

00:40:18.864 --> 00:40:19.920
So I pray that that blesses you.

00:40:19.920 --> 00:40:21.383
Let's pray together.

00:40:27.572 --> 00:40:31.830
I don't want to sit here and ramble, but I just felt it was good to say it.

00:40:31.830 --> 00:40:36.400
"Father, I just thank You, Lord, for Your body that was broken for us.

00:40:44.817 --> 00:40:45.012
" We never enter into prayer on this channel without taking communion first.

00:40:45.012 --> 00:40:45.403
Period.

00:40:45.403 --> 00:40:46.549
It's just part of it.

00:41:00.130 --> 00:41:01.679
We cover ourselves in the blood.

00:41:08.233 --> 00:41:09.312
And if the Lord wants to show us something, then He does.

00:41:30.853 --> 00:41:31.057
If He doesn't, then that's fine.

00:41:31.057 --> 00:41:35.149
But we always cover and we pray over our nation, we'll pray over whatever prayer request.

00:41:35.149 --> 00:41:36.859
But I want you to believe big today.

00:41:36.859 --> 00:41:38.600
Nothing's too big and nothing's too small.

00:41:38.600 --> 00:41:41.280
Jesus Christ paid the price for it all.

00:41:41.600 --> 00:41:54.199
And it's time for us to be believing believers that don't have doubt in us, that say, "Hey, I believe God can do it today.

00:41:54.199 --> 00:42:00.844
" Stop believing for tomorrow—always believing for tomorrow and the next day and the next day.

00:42:00.844 --> 00:42:02.356
Believe for your now.

00:42:02.356 --> 00:42:18.799
When I'm sitting there and I'm praying for my daughter Megan—you know, because Megan is overcoming special needs and she's getting better every day—He always says to me when I'm praying in the church, "Braden, why not now?

00:42:18.799 --> 00:42:20.899
Stop always thinking for tomorrow.

00:42:20.899 --> 00:42:23.359
Why not believe for now?

00:42:26.382 --> 00:42:26.667
The right now.

00:42:26.667 --> 00:42:31.428
Faith calls those things that be not as though they were right now.

00:42:31.428 --> 00:42:33.697
Speak to your mountain right now.

00:42:33.697 --> 00:42:39.404
" So I'm trying to tell you, as we take communion, believe for your circumstance.

00:42:48.187 --> 00:42:48.373
You know, you go, "Well, Brandon, I've had this for so many years.

00:42:48.373 --> 00:42:50.914
My marriage has been bad for so many years.

00:42:50.914 --> 00:42:54.360
My kids have been strung out on drugs.

00:43:02.079 --> 00:43:04.510
You know what?

00:43:04.510 --> 00:43:07.760
I believe someday the Lord's going to do this.

00:43:07.760 --> 00:43:09.040
Why not today?

00:43:09.040 --> 00:43:10.590
Why not right now?

00:43:10.590 --> 00:43:19.542
" So, as we believe today, as we take our communion right now, believe for your expiration date.

00:43:19.542 --> 00:43:35.408
It's like Billy Burke always says: if it started with a symptom, why not the absence of a symptom be the beginning of the healing?

00:43:35.408 --> 00:43:38.516
Why can't the absence of it?

00:43:38.516 --> 00:43:40.220
I always think, "Well, why not?

00:43:46.480 --> 00:43:46.960
That's good thinking, Billy.

00:43:46.960 --> 00:43:48.879
I love it.

00:43:48.879 --> 00:43:55.749
Why not have the absence of a symptom be the beginning of your breakthrough?

00:44:13.588 --> 00:44:14.413
" So let's believe that the bad report you got maybe today at the doctor that said you've got a couple of days to live, the divorce papers that you received, the husband or the wife saying, "Hey, I don't want to be married anymore...

00:44:14.413 --> 00:44:18.799
" That God can turn your marriage around, and love takes no account of a suffered wrong.

00:44:24.859 --> 00:44:25.120
And love never fails.

00:44:34.667 --> 00:44:34.960
And all the things the Bible says to us, that you can turn your marriage around even if it seems like it's the darkest hour.

00:44:34.960 --> 00:44:40.639
You may walk through the valley of the shadow of death, but it doesn't mean you have to camp there.

00:44:42.520 --> 00:44:43.080
It doesn't mean you have to camp there.

00:44:43.080 --> 00:44:50.994
I've walked many times through the valley of the shadow of death, and you think, 'Man, this looks really, really dark right now.

00:44:50.994 --> 00:44:53.890
' But you don't camp there.

00:44:56.675 --> 00:44:59.839
You get in a four-wheel-drive vehicle, you put it into first gear, and you burn rubber and get out of there.

00:45:04.286 --> 00:45:05.520
I refuse to build a camp there and say, 'Woe is me.

00:45:09.017 --> 00:45:09.166
I'm living in the valley.

00:45:09.166 --> 00:45:12.845
' Don't live in the valley of your circumstance.

00:45:13.359 --> 00:45:22.009
Believe, have an expectation that God's going to do a breakthrough in your life today.

00:45:22.009 --> 00:45:22.996
It's time.

00:45:22.996 --> 00:45:29.691
If we truly are living in the last days, we're going to start seeing these signs and wonders like we all say.

00:45:32.789 --> 00:45:34.160
And I believe we're going to see it as we see it get darker and darker.

00:45:34.160 --> 00:45:39.013
It's time for the light to get lighter and lighter on the church, on us.

00:45:39.013 --> 00:45:43.680
Father, we just thank you, Lord, for the body today.

00:45:43.680 --> 00:45:46.919
Father, I'm so grateful for what you did for us on that cross.

00:45:46.919 --> 00:45:49.840
Father, you said in your word, 'By your stripes, we are healed.

00:45:49.840 --> 00:45:52.040
' And we take this body in the name of Jesus.

00:45:52.040 --> 00:46:18.320
And we thank you, Lord, that you were wounded for our transgressions, you were bruised for our iniquities, the chastisement of our peace was upon you, and with your stripes, we are healed.

00:46:18.320 --> 00:46:19.120
